<br>
Level 20 Erudite Magician on 7th.<br>
I've reading all this stuff on how high defense keeps you alive at higher lvls and my Defense is (1). How do I go about raising it without taking a ton of damage? I'm untwinked and basically using cloth armor, mobs don't drop enough loot to cover equip and spells to.<br>
<br>
Thanks for any input. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/urazha.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Razha</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#333333>(7/31/02 7:16:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=403.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Raising Defense Skill (Please Read)</span><hr size=1> If you solo, its pretty easy.  Just use a NOT earth pet so the mob will run when its about dead.  Just before the mob is about to run, get in the mobs face and hit it a few times.  You will take some damage, you will deal minor damage, and have a chance at both off and def skillups.  You need to time it carefully, so pay extra careful attention to when the mob would normally turn and run in the fight...and just engage the mob 1-2 attack rounds before he does so.<br>
<br>
Defense is a VERY important skill, as is dodge.  Dodge will save your arse more times than you will be able to count.  If you manage to draw the attention of a high level mob, dodge is your only hope.  =)  Keep them skills maxed! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 170<br> <font color=#333333>(8/1/02 5:12:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=403.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.bellatlantic.net/~vze2rnxn/images/yorienko_avatar.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Raising Defense Skill (Please Read)</span><hr size=1> I'm level 49 now, and my AC is 400, any safe way of raising it? In tenebrous mountain those mobs hitting in 80 to 90 a pop, I would lose over a bubble health one round. I don't know any other way of raising it now.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzatalpus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zatalpus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(8/1/02 7:28:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=403.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Raising Defense Skill (Please Read)</span><hr size=1> After having researched this a bit for my cleric (retired) there's 2 easy ways:<br>
<br>
Find another mage/necro that needs defense skill ticks and duel them.  Dueling blue pets will raise skill (and pets only hit for 44).  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I've also heard a rumor about the trap in 2nd floor in ToFS giving skill raises, though it's very slow.<br>
<br>
I've been doing the Phantom Plate, tank on pull till down 1 bub, med/heal back up, repeat.  Skill's going up waaayy slow though.  Only at 65 now (level 49).<br>
<br>
Should have done this more at 29 when fighting the needlites:  really fast hits for low damage.<br>
<br>
Live and learn... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubelhaven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Belhaven</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 122<br> <font color=#333333>(8/2/02 3:59:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=403.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Raising Defense Skill (Please Read)</span><hr size=1> use the earth pet.  Stand closer to the mob than the pet for a few swings (until you're damaged as far as you feel safe, but NEVER below 20%).  Back away after the pet roots it again.<br>
<br>
It requires a blue mob taking swings at you to increase the skills.  I've never had any trouble keeping mine up doing the above while EXPing. <br>
<br>
Vermi Pejoratus <br>
Mage on Quellious <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ulionfrog.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lionfrog</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 210<br> <font color=#333333>(8/8/02 10:16:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=403.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Raising Defense Skill (Please Read)</span><hr size=1> When you get to about 29 (I think you can TRY at 24) get to the needlite cavern area (as mentioned above) and put a damage shield on your self while you have a fire pet up. You will get hit a bazzilion times a second for fairly low damage (2-22), your almost guaranteed many skill ups.<br>
<br>
Alantrix <p><img align=center src=http://board.rslhq.com/hosted/zonaxx/jetposse.jpg width=355 hight=73></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uraiyaeq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RaiyaEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#333333>(8/23/02 8:50:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=403.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Raising Defense Skill (Please Read)</span><hr size=1> There's a panther in WL that's lvl 60 and hit for 20-60.  If you can get a healer friend to go with you, you can raise your defensive skill with it.  With my main (60 druid), I never get the opportunity to get hurt since I level'd with my bf's warrior.  My ac was 870 at lvl 60 in some or all tov armor.  I tried the misty panther (I think that's the name, he's close to where pog lake is).  I maxed my defensive skill in about an hour or so.  It's really nice indeed. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=90395>Raiya</a> / <a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=90580>Jinling</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uwoonx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>woonx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 102<br> <font color=#333333>(8/26/02 7:52:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=403.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Raising Defense Skill (Please Read)</span><hr size=1> The mist panther (i think that's the name of the panther in WL) is indeed one of the best choices, since you need mobs that are light blue and up to gain skill increase and it hits weak for a lvl 60 mob. Shitloads of hp though. It is located behind the PoG tower. <p><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=75721">Woon</A>&nbsp<A href="http://tde.e-slackers.net/">&ltTDE&gt</A><BR>
Arch mage, 7th hammer<BR>
<A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=112180">Krisgor</A>&nbsp53 SK<BR>
<A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=112210">Khrana</A>&nbsp50 Shamanette of doom<BR>
 </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucasitadgato.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Casitadgato</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#333333>(8/28/02 3:42:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=403.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Raising Defense Skill (Please Read)</span><hr size=1> Also as a small note:<br>
<br>
If your Agility is below 75, raise it above.  There is a large step change in AC per Agility point going from 74 to 75 (or 75 to 76, can't remember) so I assume Agility's value in helping you learn defensive skills gets a step increase as well.<br>
<br>
Also there is a step change at 105 (or 106) and 135 (or 136),<br>
so get agility items for the skill-ups or get a shaman to give you a nice buff. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showPrevMessage?topicID=403.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showNextMessage?topicID=403.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=403.topic&index=8><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.threadControl?topicID=403.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=403.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=403.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub102.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="themagicianstowerannouncements">Administration<option value="themagicianstowergeneral">General<option value="themagicianstowerfrm32">Class Balance<option value="themagicianstowerfrm45">User Interface<option value="themagicianstowerspells">Spells<option value="themagicianstowerequipmentandquests">Quests<option value="themagicianstowerfrm28">Equi